{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>Members of this family are a variant form of exosortase, XrtO, with a dedicated target typically encoded by the adjacent gene. Members have a unique C-terminal extension very different from EpsI ([interpro:IPR014263]), the extension that many exosortases have. The targets of XrtO all are members of the PEP-CTERM integral membrane protein family ([interpro:IPR014270]), which describes a PEP-CTERM protein about 950 residues long, found in more than 15 genera so far. These PEP-CTERM proteins are unusually hydrophobic in stretches, suggesting an integral membrane location, which is unusual. About one third of the members of IPR014270 are in genomes with this protein, exosortase O, always encoded by an adjacent gene.</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure nil, :overlaps-with nil, :member-databases {"ncbifam" {"TIGR04489" "exosortase O"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "Exosortase O", "short" "Exosort_XrtO"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 0, "domain_architectures" 0, "proteomes" 21, "taxa" 217, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 98, "sets" 0, "proteins" 98, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 52}, "pathways" 0}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR030996", :literature nil, :go-terms nil, :entry-id nil, :hierarchy {"accession" "IPR019127", "name" "Exosortase", "type" "Family", "children" [{"accession" "IPR013426", "name" "Exosortase, EpsH-like", "type" "Family", "children" [{"accession" "IPR017540", "name" "Exosortase 1", "type" "Family", "children" []} {"accession" "IPR017544", "name" "Exosortase 2", "type" "Family", "children" []} {"accession" "IPR026488", "name" "Exosortase C, VPDSG-CTERM-specific", "type" "Family", "children" []} {"accession" "IPR026491", "name" "Exosortase D, VPLPA-CTERM-specific", "type" "Family", "children" []} {"accession" "IPR026492", "name" "Cy